v1.ImageProcessingRequest

This is an object that describes request to the ChRIS system to be able to process an image into a desired format

Fields:
    - imageprocessingrequestid: an autogenerated id that corresponds to the submitted job
    - patientid: The id of the patient
    - jobtype: The type of image processing job you want to run
    - jobstatus: The status of the job (e.g. 'Pending', 'Running', 'Failed', 'Success')




create an ImageProcessingRequest

POST /chrisapi/v1/imageprocessingrequests

Parameters
Type: BodyParameter
Description: Contains the image
Required: true
Schema: Valid medical image format (e.g. .dcm, .nii, etc.)
Default:

Type: QueryParameter
Name: patientid
Description: The id of the patient
Required: true
Schema: string
Default:

Type: QueryParameter
Name: jobtype
Description: The type of image processing job you want to run
Required: true
Schema: string
Default:
	
Responses
HTTP Code: 200
Description: success
Schema: v1.ImageProcessingRequest

Consumes
    - application/dicom
    - ...

Produces
    - application/json




get an ImageProcessingRequest

GET /chrisapi/v1/imageprocessingrequests/imageprocessingrequestid
	
Responses
HTTP Code: 200
Description: success
Schema: v1.ImageProcessingRequest

Produces
    - application/json




get an ImageProcessingRequest

GET /chrisapi/v1/imageprocessingrequests/imageprocessingrequestid/processedoutput
	
Responses
